  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex>B  \colon  A  \to   \mathsf {Type}</fr:tex> be a family of <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">propositions</fr:link>; fixing <fr:tex>f :  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } {Bx}</fr:tex>, it suffices to show any other <fr:tex>g : \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</fr:tex> may be identified with <fr:tex>f</fr:tex>. As <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> is a family of <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">propositions</fr:link>, we know that each <fr:tex>Bx</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
